reditLine":"by bequest to Walters Art Museum, 1931.[1] Created in early fourteenth century for Use of Arras and Paris, possibly for the marriage of Louis I of Châtillon (d. 1346) and Jeanne of Hainaut, as the Châtillon de Blois arms are depicted on fols. 19r and 81v, and the arms of Hainaut also appear in the borders, including in conjunction with the Châtillon arms on fol. 19r. The manuscript contains other unidentified heraldry, such as a bookplate and inscriptions.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.104","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.104_Binding_DD_0001.jpg"},{"ObjectID":14904,"Title":"Portrait of a Woman","Artist":"Spanish","Date":"ca. 1800","Medium":"oil on canvas","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.1722","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL7_37.1722_Fnt_BW_H75.jpg"},{"ObjectID":25620,"Title":"Portrait of a Boy","Artist":"Marie-Anne Fragonard (French, 1745-1823)","Date":"1745-1823","Medium":"watercolor on ivory; gold and silver frame set with diamonds","CreditLine":"given to Walters Art Museum, 1963.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/38.326","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL7_38.326_Fnt_BW_113.jpg"},{"ObjectID":25432,"Title":"Ewer","Artist":"Murata Seimin (Japanese, 1761-1837)","Date":"1766-1837 (late Edo)","Medium":"copper and copper alloy with an red artificial patina","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/53.119","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL9_53.119_Fnt_BW_PL90.jpg"},{"ObjectID":35208,"Title":"The Story of the Wrongly Exiled Prince as Told by the Princess of the Sandalwood Pavilion from the Khamsa (Quintet) of Amir Khusraw Dihlavi","Artist":"Mukund; Amir Khusraw Dihlavi (died ca. 729 AH/AD 1328); Muhammad Husayn Zarrin Qalam","Date":"1597-1598 (Mughal)","Medium":"opaque watercolor, ink, and gold on paper","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.624.203B","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.624.203b_Fp_DD.jpg"},{"ObjectID":35020,"Title":"The Buddha Preaches in Indra's Heaven and Descends to Earth, with Hell Below","Artist":"Thai","Date":"1885 (Rattanakosin)","Medium":"paint on cotton","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1992, by gift.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/35.187","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_35.187_Fnt_DD_AT23_41712-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":28064,"Title":"Covered Jar","Artist":"Chinese","Date":"19th century","Medium":"porcelain with enamels, gold; lai nam thong","CreditLine":"The Walters Art Museum","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/49.2797","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_49.2797_SideVwG_DD_AT21_24263-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":28628,"Title":"Bowl with Flying Birds","Artist":"Islamic","Date":"late 12th-early 13th century (Seljuq (?))","Medium":"fritware, white underglaze, blue, red, and turquoise overglaze enamel, with traces of gilding","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/48.1267","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS1_48.1267_IntA_DD_T17-tms.jpg"}]